diagram.documentation: The following matrix illustrates the alignment between the Advanced Orbital Manufacturing System (AOMS) objectives and identified stakeholder needs. This traceability matrix serves as a crucial tool for visualizing how the project's eight key objectives address the diverse range of stakeholder requirements. By mapping each objective to specific stakeholder needs, the matrix demonstrates the comprehensive coverage of the project's scope, highlights the multi-faceted nature of certain objectives, and identifies areas of particular strategic importance. Critical objectives like Autonomous Operations and Efficient Material Management play central roles, while specialized objectives ensure targeted compliance and sustainability, resulting in a balanced approach across technical, economic, and regulatory considerations. This analysis aids in prioritizing development efforts, ensuring that all stakeholder needs are adequately addressed, and provides a foundation for ongoing project management and stakeholder communication.
